SUMMARY:First Fridays Presents Leslie Archibald
DESCRIPTION:Free and open to the public \nDoors @ 7 pm\nPop-up poet @ 7:30 pm\nFeatured poet @ 7:40 pm\nOpen mic @ 8:15 pm \nInprint is proud to serve as the host for the First Fridays Reading Series. The First Fridays Reading Series is the oldest poetry series in Houston and was organized by Robert Clark from 1975-2019. Today\, First Fridays events are curated and hosted by local community members. \nThe July featured reader will be Leslie Archibald\, a Houston-based writer. When she is not writing\, you may find her photographing Houston’s unique character or dabbling in watercolors. Her visual and literary works appear in anthologies\, lit magazines\, and Houston galleries. Her chapbook Poems for a Broken 𝙼̶𝚊̶𝚛̶𝚛̶𝚒̶𝚊̶𝚐̶𝚎̶ Man (Finishing Line Press) is now available. Learn more about Leslie at lesliearchibaldwriter.com or @leslie.archibald. \nThe opening pop-up poet will be Margo Davis\, author of the recent poetry collection Uncoupling (Lamar University Press\, 2026). Her poems appear in local outstanding journals such as equinox and Synkroniciti\, as well as The Arkansas Review\, Deep South\, and Mackinaw Journal. Forthcoming poems will appear in The MacGuffin\, as well as a series for The Ekphrastic Review. Her photographs have appeared in Barcelona galleries and several journals\, and are forthcoming in Flyway. Margo resides in Houston but still thinks of herself as a New Orleanian. \nFor more information about the First Fridays Reading Series\, click here. To join the First Fridays Facebook group\, click here. \n
URL:https://inprinthouston.org/event/first-fridays-presents-leslie-archibald/
LOCATION:Inprint House\, 1520 W Main St\, Houston\, TX\, 77006\, United States
CATEGORIES:First Fridays
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://inprinthouston.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/LeslieArchibaldFFPRS-INSTA.jpg
END:VEVENT
